│ illegal.                                                                    │
│                                                                             │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis: The function scalarizeBinopOrCmp does not validate  │
│ that the insertion index is within bounds of the vector type before         │
│ extracting a scalar element from the constant vector. The match patterns    │
│ accept any constant index, and the extraction assumes the index is valid.   │
│ However, insertelement with out-of-bounds index yields poison, so the whole │
│ vector operand is poison. The transformation should bail out when the       │
│ insertion index is out of bounds because the vector is poison and           │
│ scalarization is not safe. Additionally, the extraction from the constant   │
│ vector at that same out-of-bounds index is invalid.                         │
│                                                                             │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s): We need to add a check that the insertion index  │
│ is less than the vector element count. This should be done after            │
